---
description: Project rules for the Next.js admin/product app
globs:
  - "**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow `AGENTS.md` and `.agents/skills/next-project-guidelines/SKILL.md`.

- This project uses Next.js 16. Read relevant docs in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing Next.js-specific code.
- Keep every visible UI text node in `div` or `span` only. Do not use `p` or `h1`-`h6`.
- Set typography with explicit `text-*` and `font-*` classes.
- Preserve the existing visual appearance when refactoring existing UI.
- Use flexbox and `gap-*` where it does not alter appearance. Avoid grid and left/right margin or padding in new code, but keep them when required for current spacing, alignment, or responsive layout.
- Avoid positioning in new code, but keep it when required for overlays, badges, modal layers, input icons, or current visual behavior.
- Style with Tailwind classes and existing custom components from `app/design-system`; prefer repository patterns.
- Do not revert user changes or refactor unrelated code.
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` after code changes and `npm run build` for broader Next.js changes.
